cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to extract symptoms and their status from clinical conversations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and ML techniques for processing human language. The paper also proposes novel deep learning approaches, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of AI techniques to assist medical providers, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also deals with privacy-sensitive data, which makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of medical scribes and medical providers, which makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible category.
